properties.Event_Description: On 17 October, the National Civil Guard organises a horse race outside the Munich city walls to honour the Crown Prince and Princess. The field on which it took place was named after the bride: Theresienwiese.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Horse Racing Recommendations:
1. Munich Racecourse (Riem)

properties.Event_Description: Oktoberfest is a success. The Agricultural Association commits to putting on the festival every year with a national showcase. This brings people and animals from all around Bavaria to Munich.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Agricultural Festival Recommendations:
1. Harvest Festival Exhibition

properties.Event_Description: Each year, the attractions from the previous festivals have to be bettered! So in that same spirit, balloonist Karoline Reichardt soars to the heavens at the Theresienwiese.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Balloonist Recommendations:
1. Bavarian Balloon Rides

properties.Event_Description: Each year only 18 licenses are issued to the innkeepers of Munich. Send- linger Höhe is a highly sought after area due to its scenic views.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Beer Gardens:
1. Bavarian Beer Garden

properties.Event_Description: Crown Prince Maximilian marries Princess Maria of Prussia. Oktoberfest plays a special role in the celebrations. 35 Catholic and Protestant couples come to Munich to give their wedding vows that same day.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Royal Wedding Venues:
1. All Saints Court Church

properties.Event_Description: Michael Schichtl's variety show débuts at the Oktoberfest. It has remained a fixture at the event ever since.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Modern Royal Wedding Venues:
1. Auf geht’s beim Schichtl - Wirtshaus & Theater

properties.Event_Description: The bicycle is a revolution in mobility and also for the Oktoberfest. Bicycle races are held, and the main race covers 10 kilometres.
For their festive entrance the bearers of the price flags are dressed in heraldic surcoats in the style of the Middle Ages.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Festival Costumes:
1. Traditional costume and riflemen's parade

properties.Event_Description: Prince Regent Luitpold demands more Bavarian identity. Every part of the region sends representatives in traditional dress. Where none are found, people model their style on the rural Oberland region, and the typical Bavarian dress is born.
properties.Modern_Recommendations:
Festival Costumes:
1. The traditional costume and hunters’ parade

properties.Event_Description: The Nuremberg innkeeper Georg Lang leases five contiguous plots of land at the "Wiesn" through front men and constructs a huge festival hall instead of small stalls. Lang sets new standards with his dedicated musical ensemble and clever advertising.

Georg Kunoth from Bremen composes the "Prosit der Gemütlichkeit!" (Cheers to pleasure!) for Lang's band. Real Bavarians initially resist the trivialisa- tion of their famous fest. The song has stood the test of time and continues to set the tills ringing

The anniversary celebration is staged with pomp and pageantry as a patriotic homage to the Bavarian monarchy. Fun and schadenfreude all at once. The "devil's wheel" is a classic Oktoberfest ride and today belongs to the Feldl fairground family.
Josef Ruprecht's ride is an enormous wooden construction. Only the cheap labour of the Great Depression makes this effort profitable.
Until 1959, pseudo-scientific “human zoos” put foreign people and cultures on display.
Creatures from Mars, the legless woman: The carnie creativity knows no limits when it comes to getting the punters in.
People have been shooting at such targets since the Middle Ages. This wonderful specimen celebrates the Bavarian marksmen at Oktoberfest from 1976 to 1999.

On 26 September, a right-wing extremist ignites an explosive at the main entrance. 12 people lose their lives and hundreds are injured. The terrorist attack has not been definitively solved to this day.
The "Olympia", with its five loops, is the work of Munich engineer Werner Stengel. It is still the longest and highest mobile roller coaster in the world.
